  "verdict": "Q (PR #571): is there a BODY precision BOTH #319-byte-exact AND faster than the served int4_g32 body? NO. The deployed int4_g32 body itself FLIPS the greedy argmax vs the bf16 body (heldout=0.005285412262156448, ood=0.0036255065045851993, official=0.10902948878868177; is_byte_exact=False). The ONLY precision that can be faster than int4_g32 is the coarser int4_g128 (fewer group scales), which flips at least as much; every byte-exact candidate (bf16, and int8/fp8 where exact) reads >=2x the body bytes and is strictly slower. body_strict_safe_lever_exists=False -> the body sits on the speed floor with NO faster byte-exact realization. Per-component census COMPLETE: HEAD #556 (lever=False, 252.31), ATTENTION #562 (byte-identical, no faster legal realization), BODY #571 (lever=False). all_three_components_censused=True, any_strict_safe_speed_lever_anywhere=False. This reconciles stark #536's collapse_locus=BODY with the legality picture: the body that collapses quality when baked/pruned is also the body with no faster byte-exact realization -- NO-FIRE is firmed from the last un-censused component. int4_g32 body flips are near-tie concentrated=False (flip-margin median 0.755803108215332 vs non-flip median 8.976581573486328, ~11.876878350874492x separation). "
